column17: Notes
Cilic won the toss and elected to serve. Already he bounces the ball 18 times on the very first point - that quirk of his is rather annoying.
Federer's return isn't deep enough to force the error but its pace throws Cilic off anyway.
There's a rally off a 2nd serve where Cilic's shot is called out but his challenge proves correct (the first of many) so the point is replayed Cilic still loses it with a bad smash miss.
Typical Federer low FH winner.

A drop shot return to surprise the big guy and force him to sprint uncomfortably smart play by Fed. Cilic changes his racquet mid-game before the next point - afterwards he would blame wrong tension for the bad start.
Just missed the line unfortunate for him.
What a toothless inside-out FH from Federer. Far from the last oneÉ
A high-octane FH-to-FH exchange Federer overwhelming Cilic with sheer quickness.
Federer committed to taking the ball early even when Cilic starts blasting it determined not to let Cilic yank him around the baseline.
Federer moves Cilic around nicely. Cilic is fit and makes it in time but nets when trying to go aggressive.
Finally Cilic wins a point by overpowering Federer from the baseline as he should.
Strong 2nd serve kicker.
Not a good FH approach Cilic should've made the pass IMO.
Forces a weak reply then misses the next shot - that's what I'd call "cilicing it away".
Cilic challenges an 'out' call again this time on serve and again gets it right - ace.
Federer mixing it up to keep Cilic alert.

The approach could've been better but would normally still be good enough to win given that Cilic was out of position and could barely get to the ball in time yet threaded the needle with his pass which landed right in the sideline corner of the service box.

Much talking about how the final being played indoors benefits Federer. It does but it benefits Cilic as well perhaps moreso. No indication after the match that Federer had any say in this though playing an indoor final in an outdoor major does look a bit iffy.
Great 1st serve return from Cilic. Federer still had time but didn't want to go on the defensive.
Right on the sideline.
A terrific 2nd serve landing right onto the middle of the AD half of the service line.
It's amazing how early Federer takes the ball.
Federer's return lands literally on the baseline and Cilic doesn't deal with it well.
Another deep return another error. "14 unforced errors already from Cilic."
Again Cilic challenges his serve being called 'out' and gets it right. This one was barely in though so the lineswoman is not at fault.
Federer nets trying to go DTL aggressively and Cilic finally holds.
"Australian Closed final". How original.
Half-volleyerer in action.
Lasting crowd applause.
"Oh what a shot."
Fed hitting the ball over the umpire's booth.
Yet another semi-half-volley shot by Roger.
Fooled Cilic (and myself) into thinking he's going to serve out wide went DTL instead.
"That's his quickest serve so far in the match - 214 km/h."
An awful forehand approach from Federer once again what's up with those?
Federer will be getting a good lot of service lets later on. Could be a personal record.

After missing the 1st serve Federer expertly hits the ball off Cilic's irrelevant return right into the ballboy's hands. He likes to show off that way every so often - saves ballkids some effort too. As usual a bit of applause ensues.
Cilic's fourth consecutive successful challenge. Federer's slice barely missed the line.
The approach was too spinny duly punished by Federer.
"That is ultra-gutsy."
Some fool yelling just before the ball toss. Federer didn't stop his service routine and ended up double-faulting.
Again someone yells as Federer is preparing to serve. This time he repeats the motion and gets a good serve in but loses the point anyway with an UE.
Cilic's perfect challenge streak comes to an end as he challenges an honest ace.
"Come on Roger!" when Federer is about to serve. Probably the same idiot again.
An excited "come on!" after the return flies long. "207 (km/h) his quickest serve" the commentator remarks.
Slicing from a neutral position isn't a good idea against a top opponent.
Federer refuses to go down the line clearly he's lacking confidence in that direction. Doesn't run around the backhand either as his inside-out forehands haven't been anything special.
Federer attempts to hit through a high kicker instead of slicing it. Fat chance.
Unlike Federer in the previous game Cilic makes the BHDTL finisher.
Best return of the match so far.
Right on the line. (Cilic wastes a challenge.)
"Serving aces for fun up to 16 now." LOL!
Would've been a stupendous return if only it wasn't a little bit long.
Federer tries to attack off a weakened net cord shot but nets it himself.
"There's nothing to choose between the two of them after the first four games." Indeed both won 67 points since 4-0 in the 1st.
Excellent disguise on that 2nd serve.
Federer's forehand continues to be toothless but he has other options - here using the short slice to bring Cilic forward then passing him with good margin to force the error.
Federer with a sullen look on his face after that miss - topspin backhand cannot be found as of late.
A huge "Come on!"  from Federer delighted after getting the break.
Redirecting crosscourt shots down the line still not working for Roger.

Cilic manages a surprisingly great short slice to draw Federer out of position then hits a deep backhand - should've gone inside-out but down the middle would ordinarily be good enough still - however Federer comes up with a truly magical baseline half-volley that lands on the sideline and there is nothing anyone could do against that. The best shot of the match without a shred of doubt.
Cilic's challenge goes in vain.
Gets an easy floater and miscues it completely not great.
Finally a great forehand from Federer it's been a while.
Federer pulls Cilic wide with a shallow slice return. Cilic in his befuddled state only manages a half-hearted slice that hugs the net.
Sweet low backhand and a classy volley behind the service line.
"He is unstoppable right now. He's seizing the match by the throat." Sure looks like it at the moment.

Federer seems to be in full flight with the wings of confidence while Cilic is falling one point away from going a double break down and then a Federer victory would be all but assured. The ensuing turnaround wasn't something to be expectedÉ
That return was going out but Federer volleyed it anyway. Certainly made for a prettier point.
Federer changes racquets between the games. Maybe that was a factor as well hmm.
Federer hasn't been using challenges recently must be keeping them for crunch time.
Federer throws away a challenge on an obviously long serve using it to buy himself extra time to regroup. Too bad it didn't work.
Federer's serve and forehand in serious disarray from now on until mid-5th set.
A bad call on the first rally - the challenge reveals Cilic's shot caught the inside of the line. The point is replayed Cilic wins it.
A crafty short slice return to set up the I/O FH which jumps off the net a bit and throws Cilic off.
[Both players stand at 35 winners at the moment.]
At last a good shot to win a point on serve.
Federer entertains the crowd by hitting the returned ball off a missed serve right into the ballgirl's hands again.

If only the let serve was a millimeter higher it would've been an ace. Tough luck for Federer as several of his serves just touch the net cord. But as for rally some truly top quality there for a change with several shots landing near the lines. Cilic finding confidence and showing mental composure here strong effort from him.
A brave 2nd serve ace followed by a cautious spinner that Cilic tees offÉ
Cilic's last forehand was almost a half-volley which threw Federer off. Again great effort. Federer loses another challenge.
Another slice from a neutral position another point lost.
Cilic's unreturned 1st serve is called out but his challenge proves right. He has to serve again good thing he still wins the point.
Still no good angle redirection.
Ljubicic maintains a cool and collected expression.
Federer's defensive forehand loop lands on the baseline which momentarily confuses Cilic - he ends up striking a bit late and misses.
Cilic's backhand was actually a tiny bit long (confirmed by "TV Hawk-Eye" replay) but nobody on court noticed it.
"CHUM JETZE!"
Terrific angled backhand here. Cilic wastes a challenge.
A linesman calls Cilic's serve out only to correct himself a moment later so the point must be replayed. Federer challenges in vain. "Nice call buddy" he quips afterwards.
Federer proves the line umpire wrong this time with an eagle-eyed challenge.
Cilic tried to run around and attack but the return was too deep for that.
Federer serves a slow kicker but Cilic seems overwhelmed with the multitude of options and pushes it out.
A really guttural "come on!" by Fed it's like a roar.
Although now in a winning position Federer is quite rattled. Had some talk with the umpires during the changeover.

Federer annoyed with Garner on the changeover asking him to be proactive and tell when the new balls are to be introduced. "I'm 3-0 in the 5th man." Interestingly I read Garner was the chair umpire at the USO 2009 final - remember the hilarious "when I talk I talk".
By this point Cilic is overcome by frustration. A racuous fifth set could save the match despite its share of errors instead it was a quick and - dare I say - dull ending.
Wasted challenge by Cilic.
Nice forehand near the line.

Federer is teary-eyed and relieved after winning the titleÉ but wait Cilic is challenging Roger hands on the knees a hysterical smile - he can't believe the match point challenge happened AGAIN! Not a bad challenge by any means either but of course the super kick serve was millimeter-perfect and that's the match.
